Frank Lampard will be seeking his first Champions League points as Chelsea manager, when he takes his team to France to face Lille on Wednesday. The former England midfielder saw his side lose 1-0 at Stamford Bridge against Valencia, with Ross Barkley missing a chance to level from the spot. Lille were also hammered 3-0 by Ajax in their first fixture. Kick off is 8pm West African time. Wednesday, October 2
